  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium-high heat.",
    "Season the lamb loin chops with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and ginger powder.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together the Tohoku mother sauce, yuzu juice, soy sauce, rice vinegar, Dijon mustard, and sesame oil.",
    "Add the lamb loin chops to the marinade and coat evenly.",
    "Thread the lamb loin chops onto skewers, leaving a little space between each piece.",
    "Brush the grill or skillet with a small amount of sesame oil to prevent sticking.",
    "Sear the lamb loin chops for 2-3 minutes per side, or until they reach your desired level of doneness.",
    "Transfer the lamb loin chops to a wooden board and let rest for 5 minutes.",
    "Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garnish with fresh thyme and parsley, if desired.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
